LINUX
- man <command> - documentation
- echo "..." - returns text we provide
- whoami - returns user we're logged in as
- ls - listings folders
- ls -a - listing all folders
- ls -help - help with ls
- cd - change directory
- cat - content of file
- pwd - shows full path to directory
- find -name <file/*> - finds path to file
- grep "81.143.211.90" access.log - searchs for that in acces log file
- grep -R "PRETTY_NAME" /etc/ - searches for that in whole directory
- & - makes sth in the background
- com1 && com2 - command2 will be done after com1
- echo hey > welcome - message hey in file welcome
- echo hello >> welcome - adds hello at the end


